ck Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (of Norman origin): habitational name with fused French preposition <i>d(e)</i>, for someone from Isigny in Calvados, France, named from the Gallo-Roman personal name <i>Isinius</i> (a Latinized form of Gaulish <i>Isina</i>) + the locative suffix <i>-acum</i>."],"variants":[]},{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705189,"age":9,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705190,"age":40,"year":"1290","julianDay":2192224,"title":"Jews Expelled From England","description":"After years of anti-Semitic behavior, King Edward I expelled Jews from England in 1290.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705191,"age":65,"year":"1315","toYear":"1317","julianDay":2201354,"title":"Famine Strikes Europe","description":"A famine caused by cold winters and wet summers across Europe caused millions to die due to starvation. Desperation from hunger caused high levels of crime, stampedes in bread lines in London, infanticide, and even cannibalism throughout Europe.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Sir William d'Isney I was born in 1250, in England, his father, Sir Thomas d'Isney, was 26 and his mother, Paynell, was 21. He married Berthsheba Ormesby in 1293, in Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died about 1325, in Norton Disney, Lincolnshire, England, at the age of 76."},"et":{"1250–about 1325":"1250–umbes 1325","1250–1325":"1250–1325","1253–Female":"1253–Surnud","–1293":"–1293","1224–Male":"1224–Surnud","1229–Female":"1229–Surnud","1315":"1315","1259":"1259","1325":"1325","1224":"1224","about 1325":"umbes 1325","1253":"1253","1250":"1250","1293":"1293","1317":"1317","1290":"1290","1229":"1229","England":"England","Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom":"Lincolnshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Norton Disney, Lincolnshire, England":"Norton Disney, Lincolnshire, England"},"fi":{"1250–about 1325":"1250–noin 1325","1250–1325":"1250–1325","1253–Female":"1253–Kuollut","–1293":"–1293","1224–Male":"1224–Kuollut","1229–Female":"1229–Kuollut","1315":"1315","1259":"1259","1325":"1325","1224":"1224","about 1325":"noin 1325","1253":"1253","1250":"1250","1293":"1293","1317":"1317","1290":"1290","1229":"1229","England":"England","Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom":"Lincolnshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Norton Disney, Lincolnshire, England":"Norton Disney, Lincolnshire, England"},"fr":{"1250–about 1325":"1250–environ 1325","1250–1325":"1250–1325","1253–Female":"1253–Décédée","–1293":"–1293","1224–Male":"1224–Décédé","1229–Female":"1229–Décédée","1315":"1315","1259":"1259","1325":"1325","1224":"1224","about 1325":"environ 1325","1253":"1253","1250":"1250","1293":"1293","1317":"1317","1290":"1290","1229":"1229","England":"Angleterre","Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom":"Lincolnshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Norton Disney, Lincolnshire, England":"Norton Disney, Lincolnshire, Angleterre","l